Philippine Stocks: Alliance Global, Banco de Oro, First Metro

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-25T04:27:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/philippine-stocks-alliance-global-banco-de-oro-first-metro.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.9 percent to
4,190.98, the lowest level since April 5. The measure fell for a
fifth day, the longest losing streak since March.  Alliance Global Group Inc. (AGI)  , which has investments
in property development and casino, tumbled 5 percent to 10.24
pesos, the lowest level since Oct. 6. The stock was cut to
“neutral” from “outperform” by analysts at Macquarie Group
Ltd. due to a “lack of clarity” on the earnings of the
company’s gaming venture. The tumble was the biggest percentage
loss in the Philippine Stock Exchange Index.  Banco de Oro Unibank Inc. (BDO)  , the  Philippines ’
largest bank by assets, fell 2.5 percent to 56.55 pesos, the
sharpest loss since Feb. 10. The stock was cut to “hold” from
“buy” by April Lynn Lee-Tan, an analyst at CitisecOnline.com
Inc., on concern valuations may no longer be attractive.  First Metro Investment Corp. (FMIC)  , a provider of
financial services, climbed 3.2 percent to 48.50 pesos, the
steepest gain since May 18. The company said it will pay a
dividend of 2.66 pesos per share, its highest payout since 2004.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
